their contributions to science, and their exciting adventures against the backdrop of California and world history.California's Frontier Naturalists covers all the major expeditions to California as well as individual and institutional explorations, introducing naturalists who accompanied boundary surveys, joined federal railroad parties, traveled with river topographical expeditions, accompanied troops involved with the Mexican War, and made up California’s own geological survey. Among these early naturalists are famous names—David Douglas, Thomas Nuttall, John Charles Fremont, William Brewer—as well as those who are less well-known, including Paolo Botta, Richard Hinds, and Sara Lemmon.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNatural historyzCalifornia. 0aNaturalistszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aScientific expeditionszCalifornia. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aamerican west.  abotany.  aboundary surveys.  acalifornia.  adavid douglas.  adeath valley.  aexpedition.  aexplorers.  afieldwork.  afrontier.  ageological survey.  ageology.  ajohn fremont.  ala perouse.  aland development.  aland management.  amexican war.  amonterey.  anatural sciences.  anatural world.  anaturalism.  anaturalist.  anature.  anonfiction.  apacific northwest.  apaleontology.  apaolo botta.  aplants.  arailroads.  arichard hinds.  asara lemmon.  ascience.  ascientists.  asettling the west.  athomas nuttall.  aunited states.  awild west.  awilderness.  awilliam brewer.  azoology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023010140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092750640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97805